          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-27 01:52:40" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>an object (not necessarily three-dimensional) which has been formed to resemble a person, god, animal, etc.</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>likeness</Gloss>
                <Gloss>image</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In certain contexts the referents of εἰκών[a], {L:τύπος&lt;SDBG:τύπος:000001&gt;}[b], and {L:χάραγμα&lt;SDBG:χάραγμα:000001&gt;}[b] may have special religious significance in that they may refer to idols, but the focal component for the translator is that of a likeness or resemblance (see {D:58.35}). In contexts such as {S:04002202000012} an equivalent translation may be simply ‘a picture,’ but in {S:04500102300020} and {S:04400704300030} one may use the same expression as is employed to render {L:εἴδωλον&lt;SDBG:εἴδωλον:000000&gt;}[a] ‘idol’ ({D:6.97}).</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
