            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-27 01:52:40" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>that which has the same form as something else</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>same form</Gloss>
                <Gloss>likeness</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Since the expressions τοῦ χοϊκοῦ and τοῦ ἐπουρανίου refer to individuals, it is much more satisfactory to translate {S:04601504900022} as ‘just as we have the likeness of the man made of earth, so we will have the likeness of the Man from heaven.’|In {S:04601504900022} εἰκών designates similarity in class or kind, while in {S:04500102300020} εἰκών indicates a fashioned object (see {D:6.96}).</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
